Popular comic merchant, Ayo Makun aka AY has welcomed his second child with his wife Mabel Makun. The comedian-cum-actor shared the great news via his Instagram page on Tuesday. He posted a video where he was seen holding several love shaped balloons with the inscription ‘Sweet baby girl” alongside bouquet of flowers and a teddy bear while he walked into his wife hospital room to see her and their new baby. Upon entering the room, he planted a kiss on his wife’s forehead who was partially seated on the bed and handed her the bouquet of flowers while their new born sleeps peacefully in her cot. The father of two excitedly dropped the teddy in the baby’s cot and proceeded to wash his hands so he could have a feel of their newest bundle of joy, Ayomide.   Joeboy hits 100 million streams on Boomplay     Ejike Asiegbu mourns dad     Bobrisky allegedly sets to wed ‘billionaire lover’   - Advertisement - Read Also: AY comedian: I’m happy that people are supporting Nollywood He wrote: “Our prayers in the last 13 years has been answered. “Ayomide thank you for making @realmabelmakun and I, mummy and daddy again.Thank you for making Michelle a big sisters. “Thanks to everyone who kept us in their prayers and never stopped feeding us with positive vibes. “Trust in the Lord with all your heart and lean not on your own understanding; in all your ways acknowledge Him and He will make your paths straight” “GOD’S TIME IS ALWAYS THE BEST.”